Before, I already ask you about the logic to track the keyword and you give the logic in project.md you can find it in section "DAILY KEYWORD TRACKING LOGIC FLOW:"

DAILY KEYWORD TRACKING LOGIC FLOW:
Backend Server Process (Daily Execution):

Query Keywords to Track: SELECT * FROM indb_keyword_keywords WHERE is_active = true AND (last_check_date != CURRENT_DATE OR last_check_date IS NULL)
Track Each Keyword: Call Google Search Console API to get current ranking position
Store Daily Record: Insert into indb_keyword_rank_history with today's date and position
Update Last Check: Set last_check_date = CURRENT_DATE in indb_keyword_keywords
Auto-Update Latest: Trigger automatically updates indb_keyword_rankings with latest position
Data Flow:

indb_keyword_keywords (source) 
    ↓ (daily server process)
indb_keyword_rank_history (historical data)
    ↓ (automatic trigger)
indb_keyword_rankings (latest positions)
Benefits:

Performance: Overview page loads quickly from indb_keyword_rankings (latest only)
History: Rank History page shows 30+ days from indb_keyword_rank_history
Efficiency: Server skips already-tracked keywords using last_check_date
Reliability: Trigger ensures latest rankings always stay synchronized

params = {

    "query": "football",
    "results": 100,
    "country": "us",
	"mob_search": true,
    "page": 0
}

response = requests.get(url, params=params)

if response.status_code == 200:
    data = response.json()
    print(data)
else:
    print(f"Request failed with status code: {response.status_code}")
